The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Crash crunch for Germany
                                                                                                                       7                                      Crash crunch for Germany
            QUICK TAKES                      
	Berlin: Germany striker Thomas Mueller crashed during a mountain bike run with squad members at their Italian pre-World Cup training camp, needing several stitches to his injured chin, the team said on Wednesday.         
	Meanwhile, Germany were taken by surprise when six doping testers showed up unannounced on Wednesday.         
	Six Nada (National Anti-Doping Agency) testers arrived today (Wednesday) for an unexpected doping control, a DFB spokesman informed.  
	Strange ban  
	Madrid: Vicente del Bosque, the Spain coach, has banned his players from using social network sites like Facebook and Twitter during the World Cup in an effort to prevent any outside distractions.   
	Cow cleanse   
	Johannesburg: South African tribal chiefs and healers have slaughtered a cow outside Soccer City, the biggest stadium at the World Cup, as part of rituals to appease the spirits of ancestors and welcome fans.   
	Fake fault  
	Johannesburg: Fake Cup souvenirs are costing Fifas official suppliers millions of dollars in lost sales, an anti-counterfeit organisation said on Wednesday. Fake shirts, flags and other souvenirs are available on South Africas streets  often sold by traders at traffic lights.                                                                                                                     
